Bacabal
Bacabal is a city in Maranhão, Brazil. It is located approximately 250 km south of the state capital São Luís. The city proper has a population of 104,633 (IBGE 2018 estimate).{"citetype": "web", "url": "ftp://ftp.ibge.gov.br/Estimativas_de_Populacao/Estimativas_2018/estimativa_dou_2018_20181019.pdf", "title": "Brazilian Institute of Geography and Statistics", "year": "2018", "accessdate": "6 March 2019", "quote": "2018 Estimates of Population"} It is the seat of the Roman Catholic Diocese of Bacabal.{"citetype": "web", "url": "http://cidades.ibge.gov.br/xtras/perfil.php?codmun=210120", "title": "IBGE {{!}} Cidades {{!}} Maranh\u00e3o {{!}} Bacabal", "website": "cidades.ibge.gov.br", "accessdate": "2016-05-19"}
The municipality contains a small part of the Baixada Maranhense Environmental Protection Area, a 1,775,035.6 hectares (4,386,208 acres) sustainable use conservation unit created in 1991 that has been a Ramsar Site since 2000.[3]
